theorem
Th49: ((x _|_ y0 & y0 // y1) implies x _|_ y1)
proof
assume that
A1: x _|_ y0
and
A2: y0 // y1;
A3: x,y0 are_orthogonal  by A1,CKB52:def 1;
consider r such that A4: y1 = ( r * y0 ) by A2,CKB33:def 1;
|( x,y1 )| = ( r * |( x,y0 )| ) by A4,EUCLID_4:22
.= ( r * ( 0 ) ) by A3,RVSUM_1:def 17
.= ( 0 );
then A5: x,y1 are_orthogonal  by RVSUM_1:def 17;
(x <> ( 0* n ) & y1 <> ( 0* n )) by A1,A2,CKB33:def 1,CKB52:def 1;
hence thesis by A5,CKB52:def 1;
end;
